textAfterTable: 6071 Sakitama           Discovered 1992 Jan. 4 by T. Hioki and S. Hayakawa at Okutama. Sakitama, a region of Gyoda city and from which Saitama prefecture takes its name, is known for its burial mounds, constructed from clay and rocks between the fourth and seventh centuries.
